<br>
I agree with you to an extent, but then I go look at one of Raz's reasonable, concise, calm posts.<br>
<br>
Call me grumpy, but I'm tired of all the Negative Nellie (just call me Flanders) activity on this board, when we're currently at the height of our powers. =)<br>
<br>
I agree that we all have the right to react as vehemently or calmly as we wish; it's just that I'm personally annoyed by the real vitriol we've been seeing here, our disrespect of the class, and mostly our disrespect of each other.<br>
<br>
I love being a Mage, and at times it seems to me that the Mage community-at-large believes there to be a VI conspiracy and/or total incompetence when it comes to the class.  =)<br>
<br>
The way I see it, if Mages sucked as much as the posts on this board indicate, or if VI really did as terrible a job as is sometimes made out, here, then the game or the class would have died long ago.<br>
<br>
Remember, too, we're at the very beginning of this beta phase, and only recently the addition of the &quot;player testers&quot; (as a rule) was made.  <br>
<br>
I'm optimistic. =)<br>
<br>
I think we should all take a deep breath, and give this a bit of time to work out, before we take off our collective Mage shoe and start pounding it on the table. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#333333>(9/24/02 9:52:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Expectations</span><hr size=1> Betamagician as someone said, all we have to work on is the spell data as posted on the Lucy board.<br>
