BetaMage,<br>
<br>
Point taken...<br>
<br>
...but from Verent's past history of dealing with mage issues, I for one am not surprised at the paranoid nature of mage posters here.  You know the old saying &quot;Fool me once, shame on you. Fool me twice, shame on me.&quot;?  I think mages are a bit more wise now and are more vocal in the face of years of Verent ignoring their pleas, and don't want to be fooled again.  If this comes off like whining and ranting, then I say only Verent's past policies are to blame (and the human nature of being defensive when your back is pushed up against the wall).<br>
<br>
That being said, there is still no need for some of the vitriol present here.  We can be outraged without being snide, and rant posts without offered alternatives/solutions are also of limited value.<br>
<br>
- Register your displeasure/pleasure at a spell or ability.<br>
- Offer alternatives that you believe are better.<br>
- Hope for the best.<br>
- If nothing changes, return to step one.<br>
<br>
Sage Finraziel<br>
